{
  "text": "Remark 3.7 (General block-diagonal preconditioner). This section proved results for a block-diagonal Jacobi preconditioner, where the preconditioner inverts the diagonal blocks of the original matrix. For A 22 = 0, it is known that if one of these blocks is instead the appropriate Schur complement (and is inverted exactly), GMRES converges in four iterations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Conversely, as discussed earlier, fixed-point iteration is not guaranteed to converge in four iterations (or likely ever; see Remark 2.2). However, we have been unable to identify a proof for block-diagonal preconditioning when one block is an approximation to the Schur complement, or even when one block is exactly the Schur complement and A 22 = 0.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "35457428",
    "[CITATION_2]": "32302506"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "32302506": {
      "title": "A note on preconditioning for indefinite linear systems",
      "abstract": "Preconditioners are often conceived as approximate inverses. For nonsingular indefinite matrices of saddle-point (or KKT) form, we show how preconditioners incorporating an exact Schur complement lead to preconditioned matrices with exactly two or exactly three distinct eigenvalues. Thus approximations of the Schur complement lead to preconditioners which can be very effective even though they are in no sense approximate inverses."
    },
    "35457428": {
      "title": "A note on preconditioning nonsymmetric matrices",
      "abstract": "The preconditioners for indefinite matrices of KKT form in [M. F. Murphy, G. H. Golub, and A. J. Wathen, SIAM J. Sci. Comput., 21 (2000), pp. 1969--1972] are extended to general nonsymmetric matrices."
    }
  }
}